		"description":{
			"value":"<p class=\"flavour\"><i>You attune yourself to this symbol of your god and gain insight into your deity's will.</i></p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Implement</b><b>:</b> Holy symbol</p>\n<p class=\"basics\"><b>Enhancement Bonus:</b> Attack Rolls and Damage Rolls</p><p class=\"basics\"><b>Critical:</b> +3d8 critical damage</p>\n<p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power ✦ Daily (Standard Action)</b></p><p><i>Effect:</i> You ask a single question about two possible courses of action, and a feeling of certainty informs you which course of action is most consistent with your deity's will, or if neither is consistent with it. At the DM's discretion, your deity's answer might provide some insight into the dangers and risks that course involves. These insights are never more than vague hints.</p><p class=\"subheading\"><b>Power ✦ Encounter (Immediate Interrupt)</b></p><p><i>Trigger:</i> An attack hits an ally within 5 squares of you.</p><p><i>Effect:</i> The ally gains a power bonus to all defenses against that attack. The bonus equals the phylactery's enhancement bonus.</p>",
